      "text": "# Federal Energy Regulatory Commission\n\nFederal Energy Regulatory Commission is a Government Administration company. Federal Energy Regulatory Commission employs 900 people (-6.1% YoY, -99 people) and has an annual revenue of $12.7M, founded in 1977. Headquartered in Washington, District of Columbia, United States, operates in 5 countries (including Georgia, Moldova, Philippines, and Other).\n\n## About\nMission: Assist consumers in obtaining reliable, safe, secure, and economically efficient energy services at a reasonable cost through appropriate regulatory and market means, and collaborative efforts.\n\nFulfilling this mission involves pursuing three primary goals:\n\n1. Ensure Just and Reasonable Rates, Terms & Conditions\n2. Ensure Safe, Reliable & Secure Infrastructure Consistent with the Public Interest\n3. Provide Mission Support Through Organizational Excellence\n\n## Company Details\n- Industry: Government Administration\n- Type: Government Agency\n- Headquarters: Washington, United States",
